{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771588677,"nonce":"sCkVshGGtsccU+Jnw++bP0zd/JA=","title":"Self-service GDPR data export and deletion request for borrowers","message":"Currently, data export and deletion requests require staff to act on behalf of the borrower. GDPR gives data subjects the right to request erasure and data portability directly.\n\nConsider adding a self-service flow where authenticated borrowers (via email token or similar) can:\n- Export their own personal data\n- Request deletion of their account\n\nThe current staff-mediated workflow is legally sufficient but a self-service option would reduce staff workload and improve borrower autonomy.\n\nNot urgent -- the staff workflow covers compliance requirements.","files":null}]}